def get_signal(df, i):
    if i < 50:
        return None
    
    current_sma_20 = df.iloc[i]['sma_20']
    current_sma_50 = df.iloc[i]['sma_50']
    prev_sma_20 = df.iloc[i-1]['sma_20']
    prev_sma_50 = df.iloc[i-1]['sma_50']
    
    # Check for SMA crossover
    if prev_sma_20 <= prev_sma_50 and current_sma_20 > current_sma_50:
        return "BUY"
    
    # Check for SMA crossunder
    if prev_sma_20 >= prev_sma_50 and current_sma_20 < current_sma_50:
        return "SELL"
    
    return None
results.strategy_description: Buy when SMA(20) crosses above SMA(50) from below

def get_signal(df, i):
    if i < 1:
        return None
        
    current_close = df.iloc[i]['close']
    current_sma_20 = df.iloc[i]['sma_20']
    current_rsi = df.iloc[i]['rsi']
    
    prev_close = df.iloc[i-1]['close']
    prev_sma_20 = df.iloc[i-1]['sma_20']
    prev_rsi = df.iloc[i-1]['rsi']
    
    # Buy condition: price crosses above SMA(20) and RSI < 50
    if (prev_close <= prev_sma_20 and current_close > current_sma_20 and 
        current_rsi < 50):
        return "BUY"
    
    # Sell condition: price crosses below SMA(20) and RSI > 50
    elif (prev_close >= prev_sma_20 and current_close < current_sma_20 and 
          current_rsi > 50):
        return "SELL"
    
    # Close condition: when opposite conditions occur
    elif ((prev_close > prev_sma_20 and current_close <= current_sma_20) or 
          (prev_close < prev_sma_20 and current_close >= current_sma_20)):
        return "CLOSE"
    
    return None
results.strategy_description: Buy when price is above SMA(20) and RSI < 50

def get_signal(df, i):
    if i < 1:
        return None
        
    current = df.iloc[i]
    prev = df.iloc[i-1]
    
    # Check if price touches Bollinger Band lower
    touches_bb_lower = (prev['low'] > prev['bbands_lower'] and 
                        current['low'] <= current['bbands_lower'])
    
    # Buy condition: price touches lower BB and RSI < 35
    if touches_bb_lower and current['rsi'] < 35:
        return "BUY"
    
    # Close condition: price crosses above middle BB or RSI > 70
    if (prev['close'] < prev['bbands_middle'] and 
        current['close'] > current['bbands_middle']) or current['rsi'] > 70:
        return "CLOSE"
    
    return None

def get_signal(df, i):
    if i < 1:
        return None
        
    current_price = df.iloc[i]['close']
    current_rsi = df.iloc[i]['rsi']
    current_bbands_upper = df.iloc[i]['bbands_upper']
    
    # Check if price touches or crosses Bollinger Band upper and RSI > 65
    price_touches_upper_band = (current_price >= current_bbands_upper) or \
                              (df.iloc[i-1]['close'] < df.iloc[i-1]['bbands_upper'] and 
                               current_price >= current_bbands_upper)
    
    if price_touches_upper_band and current_rsi > 65:
        return "SELL"
    
    # Close short position when RSI becomes oversold (< 30) or price touches lower band
    current_bbands_lower = df.iloc[i]['bbands_lower']
    price_touches_lower_band = (current_price <= current_bbands_lower) or \
                              (df.iloc[i-1]['close'] > df.iloc[i-1]['bbands_lower'] and 
                               current_price <= current_bbands_lower)
    
    if current_rsi < 30 or price_touches_lower_band:
        return "CLOSE"
    
    return None

def get_signal(df, i):
    if i < 1:
        return None
    
    current_macd = df.iloc[i]['macd']
    current_signal = df.iloc[i]['macd_signal']
    prev_macd = df.iloc[i-1]['macd']
    prev_signal = df.iloc[i-1]['macd_signal']
    
    # Check for MACD crossover above signal line
    if prev_macd <= prev_signal and current_macd > current_signal:
        return "BUY"
    
    # Check for MACD crossover below signal line
    elif prev_macd >= prev_signal and current_macd < current_signal:
        return "SELL"
    
    return None
results.strategy_description: Buy when MACD crosses above MACD signal line

def get_signal(df, i):

    current = df.iloc[i]

    # Strategy conditions
    rsi_above_65 = current['rsi'] > 65
    price_below_sma20 = current['close'] < current['sma_20']
    macd_negative = current['macd'] < 0
    
    sell_condition = rsi_above_65 and price_below_sma20 and macd_negative
    
    if sell_condition:
        return "SELL"
    
    # Close short position when conditions reverse
    if prev['rsi'] > 65 and current['rsi'] <= 65:
        return "CLOSE"
    
    return None

def get_signal(df, i):
    if i < 1:
        return None
        
    current_rsi = df.iloc[i]['rsi']
    current_close = df.iloc[i]['close']
    current_sma_50 = df.iloc[i]['sma_50']
    
    # Sell condition: RSI > 65 and price below SMA(50)
    if current_rsi > 65 and current_close < current_sma_50:
        return "SELL"
    
    # Buy condition: RSI < 35 and price above SMA(50) 
    elif current_rsi < 35 and current_close > current_sma_50:
        return "BUY"
    
    # Close condition: When price crosses above SMA(50) while in short position
    # or crosses below SMA(50) while in long position
    prev_close = df.iloc[i-1]['close']
    prev_sma_50 = df.iloc[i-1]['sma_50']
    
    # Price crossing above SMA(50)
    if prev_close <= prev_sma_50 and current_close > current_sma_50:
        return "CLOSE"
    
    # Price crossing below SMA(50)
    elif prev_close >= prev_sma_50 and current_close < current_sma_50:
        return "CLOSE"
    
    return None
results.strategy_description: Sell when RSI > 65 and price below SMA(50)
